   Opportunities in Fermilab's Futures" 42 45 Gilman subpanel
   recommendation: The Subpanel recommends an expanded program of R&D on
   cost reduction strategies, enabling technologies, and accelerator
   physics issues for a VLHC. These efforts should be coordinated across
   laboratory and university groups with the aim of identifying design
   concepts for an economically and technically viable facility. The scale
   and progress of this R&D program should be subject to additional review
   in about two years. VLHC Steering Committee (http://vlhc.org) Peter
